 ClearBlade Names Steve Manweiler Vice President of Product 
         










    










 






 











 









ClearBlade Names Steve Manweiler Vice President of Product

		  Seasoned technology veteran to lead the company's product vision for enterprise mobile
		

Feb 20, 2015, 06:30 ET
		  		  						
						 from   ClearBlade Inc. 











 
















































 

 




















 


AUSTIN, Texas, Feb. 20 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- ClearBlade, a leading platform for building enterprise mobile apps and services, today announced that Steve Manweiler has been named Vice President of Product. Manweiler will lead development and engineering efforts for the organization, and will be responsible for managing the expansion of ClearBlade's platform product.
Manweiler brings more than two decades of software and product development experience to ClearBlade. Most notably, he was the CTO of Vignette. As the first employee of the organization, Manweiler was instrumental in building the company's early growth, developing the initial architecture and contributing directly to its product strategy, direction and merger and acquisition activity. 
"The opportunity to lead the development of ClearBlade's enterprise solution is exciting," said Mr. Manweiler.  "ClearBlade is leading the enterprise platform movement for mobile and cloud integration."
Earlier in his career Manweiler was a Venture Fellow at AV Labs, where he utilized his deep technical skills and experience in the start up arena to grow a large range of portfolio companies. Previously he was the CTO of Troux Technologies, and held software engineering and architecture positions at both Hal Computer Systems and Hewlett-Packard.
"Steve's brings industry experience, a proven track record and a strong vision for enterprise products to ClearBlade," said Eric Simone, CEO, ClearBlade. "His vision, experience and passion for innovation make him the perfect addition to our team," added Simone.
About ClearBlade Inc.
ClearBlade is the enterprise platform for building mobile, web and Internet of Things solutions. It is deployable both in the cloud and on-premise, encrypted end to end, and scales to Internet-sized workloads. Built from an enterprise-first perspective, ClearBlade integrates the entire ecosystem of applications, data and devices, significantly reducing the time and investment required to build apps and services.
Founded in 2007, ClearBlade is headquartered in Austin, TX with additional offices in New York City, NY. For more information about the company, please visit clearblade.com.
